   <taskbody>
      <context class="- topic/section task/context ">
         <note type="warning" class="- topic/note ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">To prevent personal injury, the operator must be ready to use the service brake if the
        parking brake is not adjusted correctly and the lift truck starts to move.</p>
         </note>
         <note id="note_n4s_svz_5gc" type="note" class="- topic/note ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">Be sure area around the lift truck is clear of personnel and obstructions.</p>
         </note>
      </context>
      <steps class="- topic/ol task/steps ">
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Drive the lift truck with a rated load up a 15% incline.</cmd>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Halfway up the incline, stop the lift truck by applying the service brakes.</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
               <fig id="fig_xvx_rvz_5gc" class="- topic/fig ">
                  <image href="media/image904.png"
                         id="image_zvx_rvz_5gc"
                         placement="inline"
                         class="- topic/image "/>
               </fig>
               <p class="- topic/p ">Typical Example</p>
            </info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Engage the parking brake and slowly release the service
brake.</cmd>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">If the parking brake has the correct adjustment the lift truck
will be hold in place. If the parking brake does not hold, adjust
the parking brake.</cmd>
         </step>
      </steps>
